$ sudo apt-get update

Installing JDK 8
$ sudo add-apt-repository ppa:webupd8team/java
$ sudo apt-get update
$ sudo apt-get -y install oracle-java8-installer
$ java -version
o/p - openjdk version "1.8.0_131"
OpenJDK Runtime Environment (build 1.8.0_131-8u131-b11-2ubuntu1.16.04.3-b11)
OpenJDK 64-Bit Server VM (build 25.131-b11, mixed mode)


Installing Apache Cassandra:
Step 1: Add source list
Step 2: Add the Apache Cassandra repository keys:
Step 3: Update the repositories:
Step 4: Install Cassandra:

Step 1: Add the Apache repository of Cassandra to /etc/apt/sources.list.d/cassandra.sources.list, for example for the latest 3.11 version:
$ echo "deb http://www.apache.org/dist/cassandra/debian 311x main" | sudo tee -a /etc/apt/sources.list.d/cassandra.sources.list 

Step 2: Add the Apache Cassandra repository keys:
$ sudo apt-get install curl
$ curl https://www.apache.org/dist/cassandra/KEYS | sudo apt-key add - 
$ sudo apt-get update
Note if getting error in adding public key 
then hit "http://cassandra.apache.org/download/"


Step 4: Install Cassandra:
$ sudo apt-get install cassandra

Link "http://cassandra.apache.org/download/"
